    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-06T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-06T00:00:00-05:00" n="331"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d331">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName corresp="#p_MDH1">D. H. Miller</persName> to
                            <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Colonel E. M. House</persName>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-06">6 December,
                            1918</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Conference with <persName>Tyrrell</persName> and <persName>Crowe</persName>
                    convinces me that no program of procedure for interallied conferences can be
                    agreed on in advance and that it will be necessary for the President to have his
                    own program of subjects to be discussed and of the order of discussion. I have
                    this belief despite the expressed assent of <persName>Tyrrell</persName> and
                        <persName>Crowe</persName> to the necessity of such a program but this
                    assent was coupled with implied postponement until after arrival of
                    President.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
